        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add reset family carryover summaries",
        "body": "## Behavior or issue addressed\n\nDepends on #90239.\n\nWhen a session has been reset/rotated, the active transcript can be clean while the previous reset archive still contains the latest compaction summary. The next embedded-agent prompt therefore starts without the carryover context unless the model/tool explicitly asks for family history.\n\nThis change reuses the session-family transcript resolver from #90239 and injects the latest reset-archive compaction summary into the embedded-agent prompt context before the LLM boundary, but only when the active context does not already contain a compaction summary.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Move the #90239 family/reset transcript target resolver into a shared gateway helper.\n- Keep `chat.history(includeFamily)` on the shared resolver.\n- Pass the current session store path/entry into embedded-agent attempts.\n- Add a prompt-context transform that prepends one `compactionSummary` from reset ancestor transcripts.\n- Skip injection when the active session already has a compaction summary.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** When the active post-reset session has no compaction summary but a reset ancestor transcript has a persisted compaction row, the embedded-agent prompt context should carry the active reset-ancestor branch summary forward once before the LLM boundary.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local upstream checkout at `/home/clever/.openclaw/workspace/github/openclaw` on branch `fix/session-carryover-summary`, current head `9f0f5913989663c633424f476d2a06366342b16c`, using the real TypeScript source modules through `node_modules/.bin/tsx` and a temporary on-disk OpenClaw-like session store/transcript directory under `/tmp`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a standalone terminal smoke outside the test runner. It creates an ancestor reset archive with a newer off-branch compaction summary and an older active-branch compaction summary, then calls `resolveSessionFamilyCarryoverSummary` from the current source tree.\n\n```bash\nnode_modules/.bin/tsx - <<'TS'\n# creates a temp sessions.json, active transcript, and ancestor .jsonl.reset.* transcript;\n# writes a newer off-branch compaction and an older active-branch compaction;\n# calls resolveSessionFamilyCarryoverSummary from current head\nTS\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nactive-branch-carryover-proof ok\nhead 9f0f5913989663c633424f476d2a06366342b16c\nnewerOffBranchSummary Abandoned branch decisions.\nselectedSummary Active branch decisions.\nselectedTokensBefore 12345\nselectedFirstKeptEntryId root-msg\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The resolver ignored the newer off-branch compaction summary (`Abandoned branch decisions.`) and selected the active branch compaction summary (`Active branch decisions.`) with `tokensBefore=12345` and `firstKeptEntryId=root-msg`.\n\n**Additional validation:**\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-family-carryover.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  4 passed (4)\n\n$ node --no-maglev ./node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts -t 'maps unsupported xhigh to high effort for Claude 4.6 transport runs' --reporter verbose --maxWorkers 1 --no-fileParallelism\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  2 passed | 134 skipped (136)\n\n$ node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --threads=8\nLINT_EXIT:0\n\n$ git diff --check\nDIFF_CHECK_EXIT:0\n```\n\n**What was not tested:** Full end-to-end Telegram reset turn against a live gateway was not run locally. The smoke covers the real resolver behavior with on-disk session artifacts, and the PR also has supplemental gateway/tool regression tests.\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/session-carryover-summary",
